- like "void" , "never", is another type that functions can return.
- for a function that never produces a value - for example a function which throws an error 
- whenn an error being thrown, it crashes our code, and even if we will put a return statment after it, it will never reach it.

************************************************************************
function generateError(message:string,code:number) : never {
    throw {message:message,errorCode:code};
}
************************************************************************